   - I’m listening to you. I’m all ears.
 - **Este libro es de María.**
   - This book is Mary’s.   

## Proverbios

 - **Dime con quién andas y te diré quién eres.**
   - Tell me who your friends are and I will tell you who you are. (Birds of a feather flock together.)

## Dichos

 - **Debe de ser...**
   - It is probably...
 - **Debe ser...**
   - It ought to be...
 - **Es de lamentar.**
   - It’s too bad.
 - **Es de mi agrado.**
   - It’s to my liking.
 - **Es hora de...**
   - It is time to...
 - **Es (una) lástima.**
   - It’s a pity. It’s too bad.
 - **Es que...**
   - The fact is...
 - **para ser...**
   - in spite of being...
 - **sea lo que sea**
   - whatever it may be
 - **ser aburrido**
   - to be boring
 - **ser aficionado a**
   - to be a fan of
 - **ser amable con**
   - to be kind to
 - **ser capaz**
   - to be able
 - **ser de**
   - to belong to
 - **ser de rigor**
   - to be indispensable
 - **ser de ver**
   - to be worth seeing
 - **ser digno de**
   - to deserve, to be worth
 - **ser listo/lista**
   - to be clever
 - **ser todo oídos**
   - to be all ears
 - **si no fuera por...**
   - if it were not for...
 - **Si yo fuera usted...**
   - If I were you...

# estar 

## to be

Estar is one of the most important verbs for a beginning student to learn. In addition to the countless expressions that use estar, there is a distinction that you must make between estar and ser, which also means to be. 

